9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 749, L.D. 1130, “An Act to Advance
10 Long-duration Energy Storage Within the State”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Advance Energy Storage Within the State'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
14 following:
15 'Sec. 1. 35-A MRSA §3145, as amended by PL 2023, c. 374, §1, is further amended
16 to read:
17 §3145. State energy storage policy goals
18 The state goal for energy storage system development is at least 300 megawatts of
19 installed capacity located within the State by December 31, 2025 and at least 400
20 megawatts of installed capacity located within the State by December 31, 2030. Beginning
21 January 1, 2024 15, 2027, and every 2 years thereafter, when updating the state energy plan
22 in accordance with Title 2, section 9, subsection 3, paragraph C, the Governor's Energy
23 Office established in Title 2, section 9 may shall reevaluate and may increase the state goal
24 for energy storage system development and shall, in the state energy plan, report that any
25 increase to the goal to the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction
26 over energy and utilities matters. For the purposes of this section, "energy storage system"
27 has the same meaning as in section 3481, subsection 6.'
28 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
29 number to read consecutively.
30 SUMMARY
3311 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment requires the
3322 Governor's Energy Office, when updating the state energy plan every 2 years, to reevaluate
3333 the state goal for energy storage system development. If the office increases the goal, the
